[Claim 2]
A method for reducing the cobalt content in cyanocobalt complex-containing aqueous solutions comprising:
mixing a cyanocobalt complex-containing aqueous solution with a pH below 5.0 with a copper compound and a dithiocarbamate polymer, or mixing a cyanocobalt complex-containing aqueous solution with a pH of 5.0 or higher with an acid, a copper compound, and a dithiocarbamate polymer, thereby generating first precipitates in a cobalt-containing acidic aqueous solution with a pH below 5.0 and obtaining the cobalt-containing acidic aqueous solution containing the first precipitates;
removing at least part of the first precipitate from the cobalt-containing acidic aqueous solution containing said first precipitates;
adjusting the pH of the cobalt-containing acidic aqueous solution from which at least part of the first precipitate has been removed to above 8.0 to generate second precipitates; and
removing at least part of the second precipitate from the cobalt-containing basic aqueous solution containing said second precipitates.
